The paper deals with algorithmic randomness and computability, which are central topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the form of the use of entropy and redundancy. The development of effective betting strategies with restricted wagers is a combinatorial and probabilistic problem, which falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves logical reasoning and set theory, which are part of mathematical logic (cs.LO).
